The paper deals with lower bounds on quantum communication complexity, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also introduces a norm related to communication complexity, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper uses semidefinite programming, which is a topic in optimization and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also deals with matrices and approximation algorithms, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG), respectively.
